	<dd><a name="comment_3326" ></a>
	<p><em><strong>Tiger43</strong> replies:</em> The "Votist Party" would have one single aim. And that is to encourage people not just to vote, but for those who say they know little if anything about politics to find out and learn more. Of course the party will assist.</p> <p>True its only one policy and it wouldn`t exactly make us government material, however, that would not be the aim. Simply that the "Votist Party" would do its level best to educate people more on the subject and try and make it more intersting, with the single party aim of getting more people to vote.</p> <p>All parties whatever there views hopefuly would like us for this and  if they attempted to slag us off, it would only be detremental to themselves. Of course we could quite happily criticise them without any comeback. Plus the fact that we would be no threat to them as we are not aiming for government.</p> <p>If there are floors in this idea, taking into account I have only just thought of it, please let me know. All sensible improvements to the "Votist Party" are welcome.<br /></p>
